India Denies Killing Pakistani Civilians 
India Friday denied that Indian troops had crossed the line of Control
in Kashmir and killed at least 12 Pakistani civilians.
In a telephone interview with Xinhua, an army spokesman said this is
"totally incorrect" and it is a "false" report.
According to a Reuters report, Pakistan on Friday accused Indian
soldiers of crossing a cease-fire line in the disputed region of
Kashmir and killing at least 12 people.
